      • normalize

        public void normalize()
        Description copied from class: StandardObject
        Normalize the fields of the object. The idea is to clean up the values of fields when possible (e.g. all uppercase letters, empty collection).

        It is expected that implementations of normalize will never throw an Exception. Work done during normalization should be tolerant of bad vales (e.g. null). If there's something wrong with a value, StandardObject.validate() will catch it.

        In StandardImmutableObject, the object is guaranteed to be mutable at the point normalize is called.

        StandardObject.validate() is called after normalization. The idea is that you are given a chance to fill in/correct fields before a validation check is made.

        Specified by:
        normalize in class StandardObject<Stringable>
